Five years ago Vs now ⁣
⁣
This popped on my memories today and made me reflect on how so much has changed in the past five years. ⁣
⁣
From being out on the drink 5 days a week (sometimes more), to now not having any drink for 4 years.
⁣
From career, friendship circle, lifestyle, fitness, everything. ⁣
⁣
Although no regrets, I’m very thankful to how I decided to change everything I did to be a much happier and healthier person. ⁣
⁣
Keep grinding ⁣
⁣
⁣

Overcome the barriers. ⁣
⁣
I know my strength is there, but my mind is the one that lets me down. ⁣
⁣
As soon as that weights on the bar that “makes me nervous” it’s all or nothing, make or break. ⁣
⁣
Whilst I always feel gutted when it doesn’t go to plan, I always look back and remember, once it was 80kg that was my block, then it was 90kg, now it’s 100kg. ⁣
⁣
I’ve hit 100 multiple times, and I know it’s there, it’s there with more, just timing and patience is needed. ⁣
⁣

From snapping my wrist to now, going into the 12th week since fracturing the wrist, I’m very happy with where things are falling back to. ⁣
⁣
I didn’t skip one boring session, I did my rehab, I worked with what I had and what I didn’t have. ⁣
⁣
I got my head down, I didn’t even cry 😂⁣
⁣
I’m very happy with myself and how I handled this. ⁣
⁣
Regardless of the outcome of the comp in a couple of weeks, I’ll still be happy I even made it out there! ⁣
⁣
Can’t thank @cxf_weightlifting and @fivephysio enough ⁣
⁣

My little heart is so happy😭⁣
⁣
12 weeks post breaking my wrist, and I compete for the last chance to hit a new total to qualify for British Championships ⁣
⁣
Walked away with 96kg snatch & 126kg clean and jerk, both competition PBS, hitting the total I needed. ⁣
⁣
I went with one goal, and that was the goal. ⁣
⁣
Thanks to my epic coach, for the work whilst injured, on the day and everyday - @cxf_weightlifting 
⁣
Kane, the man that fixed me, saw me every week, made it happen @fivephysio 
⁣
@sinead.feedfuelperform for taking 95% of my dramas away! 🫶🏽⁣
⁣
My top supporters leading up and on the day @clocro @__sagarp__ @harryoxley_ 
⁣
I’m absolutely buzzing and can’t stop smiling! 🫶🏽⁣
⁣
⁣
#fitness #olympicweightlifting #muscle #strength #passion #whatinjury #letsgo

To wrap up an epic week⁣
⁣
I get to go compete at British Championships for the first time ever 😭⁣
⁣
I had to come back strong and quick after injury at the start of the year to qualify for this, it was a goal of mine for 2023 that I thought had been taken away from me. ⁣
⁣
I persevered, I trained hard, I stayed in my lane. ⁣
⁣
Even getting the invite for this, I feel like a winner. ⁣
⁣
The best is yet to come 🫶🏽😭⁣
⁣
